**Envelope settings **allows you to decide how to subdivide Shipments into Envelopes if a subdivision is necessary. You can also indicate which types of non-customized inserts are to be inserted during mailing, so that space can be made for them by reducing the number of sheets in each envelope.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

In the most common Envelope Management settings, just one Envelope is used for each Shipment, complete with non-customized inserts if required. If the Shipment has to be subdivided into more than one Envelope, you can decide which of them will have a cover.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Warning

The look of the covers is configured in the Page Masters and Project views. The envelopes settings require the following parameters. The value of each parameter is entered by means of an attribute.

**Name**

**Description**

**Capacity**

Indicates the capacity of the Envelopes as a number of sheets. The value is only considered if the Shipment has to be subdivided into more than one Envelope.

**Destination Lot**

Indicates the Processing Lot to which the Envelope will be assigned. If you have configured more than one Processing Lot, you need to create an attribute to allow switching from one Lot to another.

**Multienvelope**

Boolean Value. Indicates whether or not the Shipment is to be subdivided into more than one Envelope.

**Cover**

Boolean Value. Indicates whether or not a cover is to be used for Envelopes after the first. The value is only considered if the Shipment has to be subdivided into more than one Envelope.

**Cover on first envelope**

Boolean Value. Indicates whether or not a cover is to be used for the first Envelope. The value is only considered if the Shipment has to be subdivided into more than one Envelope.

**Additional sheets : First envelope**

Indicates the number of extra sheets in the first Envelope. When calculating the actual capacity of the Envelopes, the number of sheets indicated is set aside for the inclusion of sheets not managed by Document Composition.

**Additional sheets : All envelope**

Indicates the number of extra sheets in all the Envelopes.

## Accessing the envelopes settings
In the **Output settings **exploration panel, click on **Envelopes**.

## Configuring the envelope creation mode
- Drag a Number type attribute into the **Capacity **box.

- Drag a String type attribute into the **Processing Lot **box.

- Drag a Boolean type attribute into the **Multienvelope **box.

- Drag a Boolean type attribute into the **Cover **box.

- Drag a Boolean type attribute into the **Cover on first Envelope **box.

> Warning

An attribute must be supplied for each property. System attributes which express the constants true ( Constant: true ), false ( Constant: false ), and zero ( Constant: zero ) are available for the most common configuration.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Configuring additional sheets
The actions described below apply to the **additional sheets **section.

- Drag a Number type attribute into the **First envelope **box.

- Drag a Number type attribute into the **All envelopes **box.

> Warning

An attribute must be supplied for each property. A System attribute expressing the zero constant ( Constant: zero ) is available for the most common configuration. ( Constant: zero ).

## Managing typographic inserts
This feature allows to use externally managed sheets in the envelopes. The sheets will be inserted by the print provider at print time, and envelope management will reserve the appropriate space in each envelope, updating the sheet distribution.

Up to 4 independent configurations, identified by the label **Insert 1 **to **Insert 4**, can be created.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Option**

**Description**

**Enable typographic inserts**

Allow to use externally managed sheets in the envelopes.

**Label**

Insert a string attribute to assign a label used to identify the insert configuration.

**First Envelope**

Enable the use of externally managed sheets only in the first envelope. Drag a boolean attribute into this field.

**All envelopes**

Enable the use of externally managed sheets in all envelopes. Drag a boolean attribute into this field.

**Sheets**

Number of externally managed sheets for the envelope. Drag a numeric attribute into this field.

**Insert1 ... Insert 4**

Identify the 4 configurations allowed, in column format.
